    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow in CRC indication handling\n\n### Summary\nThe LTE eNB PHY procedures contained a critical buffer overflow vulnerability in the `fill_crc_indication` function and related indication functions. These functions used incorrect bounds checking assertions that allowed writing past the end of allocated arrays.\n\nWhen the eNB processed multiple UEs with CRC indications in the same subframe, the functions could access memory beyond their allocated pdu_list arrays, leading to memory corruption and potential crashes.\n\nThis fix corrects the bounds checking assertions in all indication functions to properly prevent buffer overflows.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SCHED/phy_procedures_lte_eNb.c`: Fixed bounds checking assertions in `fill_crc_indication`, `fill_rx_indication`, `fill_ulsch_cqi_indication`, `fill_ulsch_harq_indication`, `fill_uci_harq_indication`, and `fill_sr_indication` functions.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure eNB with multiple UEs transmitting PUSCH\n2. Ensure high traffic load causing multiple CRC indications per subframe\n3. Run eNB until `number_of_crcs` reaches `NFAPI_CRC_IND_MAX_PDU` (100)\n4. Observe potential segfault or memory corruption when accessing `crc_pdu_list[100]`\n\nThe issue manifests as intermittent crashes during high load scenarios, particularly with many UEs active in the cell.\n"
}